@startuml Authentication_Flow
!theme plain
title EduDesk - Authentication & Login Workflow

skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor #496E96
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #2D2F31
skinparam ActivityFontColor #FFFFFF
skinparam DecisionBackgroundColor #F000FF
skinparam DecisionBorderColor #2D2F31
skinparam DecisionFontColor #FFFFFF

participant User
participant "LoginScreen\n(UI)" as UI
participant "AuthService\n(Business Logic)" as Auth
participant "DatabaseSetup\n(ORM)" as DB
participant "SessionManager\n(State)" as Session
participant "NavController\n(Router)" as Nav

User -> UI: 1. Open Application
activate UI

UI -> DB: 2. init() DatabaseSetup
activate DB
DB -> DB: Connect to SQLite
DB -> DB: Create schema if needed
DB -> DB: Seed test users (4 default)
deactivate DB

UI -> UI: 3. Display LoginScreen\n[Email/NIM + Password fields]

User -> UI: 4. Enter credentials\nEmail/NIM + Password

UI -> Auth: 5. login(nim, password)
activate Auth

Auth -> DB: 6. Query Users table\nWHERE nim OR email = ?
activate DB
DB -> DB: Execute parameterized SQL query
alt User Found
    DB -->> Auth: Return User object + password_hash
    deactivate DB
    
    Auth -> Auth: 7. Verify BCrypt hash\nBCrypt.verify(password, hash)
    alt Password Correct ✅
        Auth -> Session: 8. setLocalUser(user)
        activate Session
        Session -> Session: Store User in memory\nSetup global state
        
        alt Supabase Enabled?
            Session -> Session: Sync to Supabase\nREST API call
        else No Supabase
            Session -> Session: Continue offline mode
        end
        
        deactivate Session
        
        Auth -->> UI: Return success + user
    else Password Incorrect ❌
        Auth -->> UI: Return error\n"Invalid password"
        deactivate Auth
        UI -> UI: 9. Show error toast
        UI -> User: Request credentials again
        User -> UI: Re-enter credentials
        UI -> Auth: login(nim, password)
        activate Auth
        ' ... retry loop continues
    end
else User Not Found
    DB -->> Auth: Return null/empty
    deactivate DB
    Auth -->> UI: Return error\n"User not found"
    deactivate Auth
    UI -> UI: 9b. Show error toast
    UI -> User: Request credentials again
end

deactivate Auth

UI -> Session: 10. Retrieve current user
activate Session
Session -->> UI: Return user object
deactivate Session

UI -> Nav: 11. Route based on user.role
activate Nav

alt User is STUDENT
    Nav -> Nav: Route to HomeScreen
    Nav -->> UI: Compose StudentUI
else User is INSTRUCTOR
    Nav -> Nav: Route to InstructorDashboard
    Nav -->> UI: Compose InstructorUI
else User is ADMIN
    Nav -> Nav: Route to AdminDashboard
    Nav -->> UI: Compose AdminUI
end

deactivate Nav

UI -->> User: 12. Display Role-Based Dashboard
deactivate UI

note right of Auth
    **Supported Default Test Users:**
    1. admin@edudesk.com / admin123 → ADMIN role
    2. instructor@edudesk.com / instructor123 → INSTRUCTOR role
    3. student@edudesk.com / student123 → STUDENT role
    4. student2@edudesk.com / student123 → STUDENT role
    
    **Security Notes:**
    - All passwords hashed with BCrypt (cost factor applied)
    - Session stored in memory (SessionManager)
    - Optional Supabase sync for cloud backup
    - Timeout logout after inactivity (configurable)
end note

@enduml
